<br>
I'll use Fennin as an example, but the same could apply to any devasting Rampaging mob, such as Magmaton or Solusek Ro.<br>
<br>
From the first time my guild fought these mobs, we adopted the obvious approach of single tanking the mob in the open, leaving melees to use purely ranged attacks, and just killing the mobs with spells.  Considering that a wizard will vastly outdamage most melee, it doesn't seem like all that much dps is lost using this method.<br>
<br>
On Rallos Zek, our melees melee RZTW, as even if you get hit with the AE rampage, it's hardly an issue, just back out and get a heal.  His melee isn't really devastating.<br>
<br>
Mobs like Fennin and Magmaton are devastating, and melees can find themselves one rounded if they are a couple inches too close, and I do mean inches.<br>
<br>
The question I have for those who melee these mobs is - why?  On mobs like Fennin you can have a cleric chain with unlimited mana, and he is easily single tanked.  The risk of retards low health aggroing and moving the mob in question out of position is much higher than if they just stay safely away plunking arrows.  Having melee in the fight can shave maybe a couple minutes off the fight, but honestly, who really fails Fennin due to lack of dps?  Who fails Magmaton due to lack of dps?  Why involve melee at all when the risk of death and a screwed up raid are there? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 375<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 12:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'll use Fennin as an example, but the same could apply to any devasting Rampaging mob, such as Magmaton<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not specifically adressing your concern, but magmatons rampage is not AE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ainmer>Ainmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 12:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ainmer.homestead.com/files/roland.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Indeed Magmaton is not AE rampage, but it really doesn't matter.  He hits hard enough to make rampage tanking him prohibitively difficult.  <br>
<br>
Once again, what is the point of melees, even if you can avoid the Rampage?  It's questionable gain for much increased risk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=broddathep>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 2:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Magmaton isn't hard to rampage tank.  Just have a warrior peel him.  <br>
<br>
Next, why not have mellee attack these mobs?  You say low health agro...  Why would that mellee be running off at low health.  That is just plain stupid.  If done right the mellee just get low health, get turned on, and then go splat.  But at least they got some damage done instead of throwing shissar fangs at the mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coray>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't consider over aggro by melee in melee range a big deal because they will just get turned on and killed and won't really alter the fight much.<br>
<br>
As sad as it sounds, a lot of classes don't even approach our ranged damage, so they're basically dead weight more than extra warriors are.  It just makes sense if you have them all on their own as far as their lives, and realize that over aggro like that doesn't usually affect much.<br>
<br>
There are fights where it still may make sense to keep everyone back, it's just not necessarily the rule on anything with AE rampage over say 1500, or big aoes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1078<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 3:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1>  I'll take a rogue doing 9k+ damage per minute over one doing 1k any day of the week. If he dies, so what. Did more in that short time meleeing than in a whole fight throwing his crap at the mob like a furious monkey. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ainmer>Ainmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 3:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ainmer.homestead.com/files/roland.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> But my point is, this melee damage isn't even necessary.  So why do it?  You can easily do Fennin flawless every time, leaving little to the chance that a melee wanders a few inches too close and gets one rounded. <br>
<br>
Clearly the mobs like this need a lot more hit points, or much higher resists.  As it stands, there's no reason to even take the risk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1080<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 4:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1>  To kill them faster?<br>
<br>
 Some nights we're lucky to get 5 clerics on. That can't last forever against a massive damage mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ainmer>Ainmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 6:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ainmer.homestead.com/files/roland.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> 5 clerics + necro + bard song = infinite mana. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ainmer>Ainmer</A> at: 3/18/03 6:21:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1081<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 6:52 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1>  That's wishful thinking, at best=P But whatever, let's assume everything goes perfect. No spot heals needed anywhere etc etc. Maybe some people like doing some actual damage? And if they can without screwing the raid why not? Shockingly enough people like to actually contribute to killing boss mobs. And since we're assuming perfect execution having people melee would be preferable anyways.<br>
<br>
*shrug* You wanted reasons. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A> at: 3/19/03 2:35:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heypam>Heypam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 1:01 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> grimmlok is ur magelo old?<br>
<br>
if not i think the ae rampage issue doesnt really apply till u fight mobs like Sol Ro or mobs in some of the elemental planes... nothing before that really requires melee using ranged...<br>
<br>
-kriegar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1076<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 2:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1>  Killed RZ this week. Tactics &gt; Gear. We're pretty casual and I'm not greedy about gear, doesn't mean I can't do simple math=P<br>
<br>
 No fight &quot;requires&quot; melee using ranged. It might be lower risk. but a good tight fight and melee on their toes and AE ramp will not hit you in most of these fights people complain about. Easier to use ranged? Yes. But he asked why anyone would do it the other way, I gave answers. If you think what I said is wrong feel free to argue and give better reasons why someone might wanna melee these melee-able mobs.<br>
<br>
 I wouldn't know, obviously I'm still trying to master the Ghoul Lord encounter with my band of newbies in tow.<br>
