<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fohguild.org/images/WarlordGinko.jpg">Here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A> at: 3/19/03 2:37:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nibben01>Nibben01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 2:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> The space between a mobs hit box and AE rampage range must be VERY VERY small.  <br>
<br>
One time on RZ I inched up to his melee range really slowly and I didn't get hit.  Every other time I've tried I've gotten hit.<br>
<br>
So how small is the difference?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karthunk>Karthunk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 4:21 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> You don't even have to rampage tank Magmaton or Sol Ro. The area that they can rampage someone in is TINY. Is it best to just solo tank these mobs and use your melee on ranged attacks? Well, I dunno. It sure does makes things very easy to control having no one taking any rampage dmg. As far as a fight taking a much shorter period of time, we drop Magmaton in less then 3 mins with all of our melee chunking ranged attacks and me solo tanking him. It really doesn't need to be faster then that. <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110313 target="_blank">Just another dead tank</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 377<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 10:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> 3-4 druids can easily keep a defensive rampage tank alive on magmaton.<br>
<br>
All of your melee doing full melee damage &gt; the added DPS of 3-4 druids nuking.<br>
<br>
Anyway, why do it? Because you should always use your guilds skills to the fullest efficiency.  The longer fights go on, the more chance there is you will lose, always.<br>
<br>
I dont know if you come from a guild that raids with 100 people, but for my guild, every mob that AE rampages usually makes it past the warriors disc.  This means either we tank swap, which is inhernetly risky to the clerics, or we attempt to single tank.  Single tanking even quad 3k+ hitting mobs like Magmaton is very possible without disc, we do it all the time, but no matter how good your healing crew is, there is always the possibility of the mob one rounding your tank and DI not firing.<br>
<br>
I agree that AE rampage should be severely toned down in PoP.  Its debilatating to melee on these encounters while leaving casters 100% intact. There are almost no fights in PoP where casters cannot function at 100%.  Add that to the fact that casters are alread outdamaging melee by 50-100% in these short encounters and it makes melee feel pretty much useless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnimwit>Gnimwit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 2:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Useless my ass, I'm busting a kick ass 15dps with my bow! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160002"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mysite.verizon.net/res00jhn/gnimtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karthunk>Karthunk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 10:02 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Raid with 100 people? No, our total guild roster is 100 people. Our last kill on Magmaton had 65 people show and he died before my defesive dropped. This was me solo tanking and the melee using ranged attacks. <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110313 target="_blank">Just another dead tank</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/03 12:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Why use melee on AE rampage mobs?  Because they die faster.  Mobs that die faster are inherently easier.  And even if difficulty isn't an issue, why wouldn't you want to kill something faster if you could?  As long as you've a nice corner, it's pretty trivial to dodge the AE rampage.  As long as one person can find a spot, so can everyone else using that person as a reference point.  The serious AE rampagers hit so hard that often a person wouldn't be able to move the mob easily even if he tried because he'd be dead too fast if he stepped too close.<br>
<br>
That doesn't mean I think it's fair that melees have to tiptoe outside AE rampage range while casters can do whatever they want, of course.  I don't think adding more HP is the answer because casters will still be more useful unless you make fights last 10+ minutes but that's just going back to Luclin boredom.  More resists in boss wouldn't be a bad idea, but there's an annoying dilemma.  Anything that can e slowed reliably has no real resistance to anything on the MR line, and 3 out of the 4 int casters has a good nuke on that line.  Every mob can be immune to all elements except MR, and I think int caster damage would still easily outclass melee DPS (except Necros).   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1079<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/03 3:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1>  Cut AE ramp range by 25%. Casters would still have an easier time of it, but that's one of their benefits. Would still keep melee on their toes, but would have more than a 5 foot space to be safely meleeing from. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=broddathep>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/03 12:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Our last kill on Magmaton had 65 people show and he died before my defesive dropped.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, many guilds raid with different compositions.  Some are strong ranged, some still have a lot of mellee since they haven't all quit and made casters/rangers yet.  And some guilds are lucky to field 40 people in the planes.  <br>
<br>
I don't believe that there is a range that you can safely mellee a rampaging mob.  I am very methodical about this and I am very adept at moving my character around.<br>
<br>
On RZ fight, we corner him and I can have him directly east of me.  I them get hit by a rampage so I move out a bit.  I can't hit him now, I tap my forward button and I get rampaged again.  Ok.  I move back and trun a tad to my right as a SLOWLY strafe into his hit circle.  Bam get hit again by rampage.  Then there are times where I am able to hit him without being rampaged.  HOWEVER, I can't duplicate it 100% of the time.  And on a very controlled fight like RZ I should be able to do so.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 887<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/03 1:32 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE Rampage and Melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> Sending melee in on the huge AE rampage mobs is a waste of time and mana. I would rather have the melees sit back and plunk away at 15dps on a mob that takes less than 3 minutes to kill. The alternative is to have a bunch of melees die and need to be rezzed and rebuffed, which just slows things down a lot more than the negligible amount of time you would save by sending all the melees in and having half of them die to rampage. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
